.TH "ima_post_load_data" 9 "ima_post_load_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ima_post_load_data \- appraise decision based on policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ima_post_load_data
.BI "(char *buf "  ","
.BI "loff_t size "  ","
.BI "enum kernel_load_data_id load_id "  ","
.BI "char *description "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
pointer to in memory file contents
.IP "size" 12
size of in memory file contents
.IP "load_id" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "description" 12
\fIid\fP-specific description of contents
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Measure/appraise/audit in memory buffer based on policy.  Policy rules
are written in terms of a policy identifier.

On success return 0.  On integrity appraisal error, assuming the file
is in policy and IMA-appraisal is in enforcing mode, return -EACCES.
